# Reference Usage

- Before product or architecture changes, read the relevant files under `docs/reference/product/`.
- Before UI implementation, read `docs/reference/design/design-notes.md` and inspect the supplied screenshots and prototype.
- `docs/reference/forum-prototype.html` is a visual reference, not production source code.
- Do not copy third-party website code, branding, text, icons, or layouts verbatim.
- Preserve this project's own identity, security rules, and accessibility requirements.
- Before using version-sensitive framework behavior, consult the relevant official documentation listed in `docs/reference/technical/official-sources.md`.
- A URL listed in a reference document is not proof that it was checked. Report which official source was inspected for version-sensitive decisions.
- Prefer project files and official documentation over community tutorials.
- Do not add dependencies solely because a reference website or prototype uses them.
- If reference files conflict with `.cursor/rules`, stop and report the conflict before changing code.

## Öncelik Sırası

1. `.cursor/rules/` — mimari, güvenlik, yetki, moderasyon
2. `docs/project/STATE.md` — yaşayan proje hafızası
3. `supabase/migrations/` — veritabanı şeması
4. `docs/reference/product/` — ürün tanımı ve akışlar
5. `docs/project/DESIGN_MEMORY.md` — UI/UX hafızası (UI sprintlerinde)
6. `docs/project/TEST_MATRIX.md` — manuel test matrisi (test/güvenlik sprintlerinde)
7. `docs/reference/design/` — tasarım yönü
8. `docs/reference/technical/official-sources.md` — resmî teknik kaynaklar
9. `docs/reference/forum-prototype.html` — yalnızca görsel referans
10. `.cursor/skills/` — proje özel inceleme ve test prosedürleri

